Heads up: you have to be 21 to even sit down in this restaurant. This was nowhere to be found on their website, there were no signs in the restaurant and nobody felt necessary to mention it to us until we had sat down and gotten comfortable. 2/3 of us were 21 and they told us we had to leave, even though we weren’t getting alcohol. I’m not going to rail on a business for their policies but the LEAST they could do is mention this on their website or have the hostess ask if you’re of legal age before seating you. City parking isn’t cheap so for us to have to leave minutes after sitting down is absurd. Staff and protocol seemed very unprofessional. I’ve lived in the city for five years and I have NEVER been told I can’t eat at a restaurant because I’m not 21. Keep in mind- we went at 1pm on a Wednesday. I could understand this if it was Saturday at 9pm. We ended up going to Jake Melnick’s Corner and Tap and let me tell you, everything happens for a reason because their service and food was out of this world!!

I've tried to give this place the benefit of the doubt and every single time they're a disappointment. They have great/unique food, but literally the worst customer service I ever received; if I compiled a top 10 of worst experiences, they'd be on it 4 times. First time they took 20 min before they asked us what we wanted, another 40 to deliver it. 2nd time was cold food and again, super late helping us. 3rd time we were missing items.  This 4th time I didn't want to bother with sitting in so I ordered pick up and they still managed to screw it up! I look up the prices online, call in and order, she tells me it's more expensive and I correct her, said the online price. She said "nevermind, it'll be ready in 15". I go in and they're overcharging me $2; I don't care about the price, it's the justification at this point. She tells me that the online menu "has been outdated for a long time", tells me I have to pay new price. Ask for manager, "manager isn't here". Should have asked for her name because she is horrendous in customer service and just argued with a wall for 5 min. I get someone "higher than her", hears me out, agrees with me and changes it in 30sec.  My experiences here are not back to back because I believe in second chances and don't believe that a restaurant service can be that consistently bad, so I'd like to note that these 4 experiences are over the course of 2+ years. Seriously, just don't bother with this place unless you like getting disappointed.
